WEBVTT

00:09.926 --> 00:12.846
<i>[somber orchestral music]</i>

00:12.846 --> 00:17.559
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:17.559 --> 00:20.562
[crowd jeering]

00:20.562 --> 00:22.939
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:22.939 --> 00:26.401
[speaking French]

01:05.607 --> 01:12.530
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:35.053 --> 01:38.431
[flames crackling
and whooshing]

01:38.431 --> 01:41.768
[Templars screaming]

01:41.768 --> 01:48.733
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:52.195 --> 01:55.115
[Tempars' screaming echoing]

01:55.115 --> 01:59.869
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:59.869 --> 02:03.164
[bell tolling]

02:03.164 --> 02:06.334
[embers hissing]

02:40.326 --> 02:43.163
[men yelling in French]

02:43.163 --> 02:45.999
<i>[tense music]</i>

02:45.999 --> 02:49.502
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:49.502 --> 02:52.213
[speaking French]

02:58.303 --> 03:00.680
[speaking French]

03:08.396 --> 03:11.608
[all laughing]

03:42.180 --> 03:44.891
[speaking French]

03:56.111 --> 04:03.284
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:40.613 --> 04:43.825
<i>[mournful music]</i>

04:43.825 --> 04:48.830
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:17.192 --> 05:20.153
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

05:20.153 --> 05:27.118
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:30.246 --> 05:33.166
<i>[light upbeat music]</i>

05:33.166 --> 05:37.921
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:52.852 --> 05:55.689
Right, Apollo, me old friend,
today's the day.

05:55.689 --> 05:57.691
We're finally getting off
this horrible rock.

05:57.691 --> 06:01.236
[Apollo purring]
Oh, yes we are.

06:01.236 --> 06:04.364
Lock in me good shit.

06:04.364 --> 06:05.907
Actually, a lot of shit.

06:05.907 --> 06:08.201
[trills]

06:08.201 --> 06:09.327
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:09.327 --> 06:11.246
So cheers, me old mucker.

06:11.246 --> 06:13.957
Tonight, we fly.

06:13.957 --> 06:15.500
True saltpeter,

06:15.500 --> 06:17.168
Peter Piper picked a peck
of pickled pepper.

06:17.168 --> 06:18.920
[muttering]

06:18.920 --> 06:25.885
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:31.933 --> 06:35.103
Houston, this is middle
of fucking nowhere.

06:35.103 --> 06:37.814
We are going for launch
after years

06:37.814 --> 06:42.527
of scraping potassium nitrate
off tree bark and cat turds.

06:42.527 --> 06:44.446
Do you copy?

06:44.446 --> 06:47.282
[imitates static]
Roger that.

06:47.282 --> 06:49.951
Commencing countdown

06:49.951 --> 06:55.123
in T-minus ten,

06:55.123 --> 06:58.585
nine, eight, seven...

06:58.585 --> 07:02.672
- [purring]
- Six, five, four,

07:02.672 --> 07:04.215
three--come on!

07:04.215 --> 07:06.468
Two, one.

07:11.598 --> 07:15.143
Come on, come on.

07:15.143 --> 07:17.145
Come on.

07:18.480 --> 07:19.898
[Apollo meows]

07:27.489 --> 07:30.784
[explosion]

07:30.784 --> 07:33.703
<i>[Handel's "Messiah" playing]</i>

07:33.703 --> 07:35.830
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:35.830 --> 07:37.290
Ha, ha!

07:37.290 --> 07:39.501
Ha! Apollo!

07:39.501 --> 07:42.671
Look at it! [laughs]

07:42.671 --> 07:43.755
Look what we did!

07:43.755 --> 07:45.548
- [trills]
- We did it!

07:45.548 --> 07:48.343
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:48.343 --> 07:52.681
How about that, dear Apollo?

07:52.681 --> 07:56.476
And now we wait.

07:56.476 --> 07:59.479
<i>[operatic vocalizing]</i>

07:59.479 --> 08:00.689
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:03.858 --> 08:08.029
[ship's horn blares]

08:08.029 --> 08:09.614
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:09.614 --> 08:12.575
<i>[warm orchestral music]</i>

08:12.575 --> 08:19.749
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:34.556 --> 08:38.351
[sobbing]

08:38.351 --> 08:40.478
[meows]

08:40.478 --> 08:44.190
[purring]

08:44.190 --> 08:47.152
[speaking Korean]

08:57.579 --> 08:59.914
Welcome back, Mr. Schrodinger.

09:03.918 --> 09:07.380
Can I ask you what year
it is, please?

09:07.380 --> 09:09.841
2023.

09:09.841 --> 09:12.719
I--it's been ten years?

09:12.719 --> 09:16.806
And 56 days
since you went missing.

09:16.806 --> 09:19.559
You were pronounced dead
shortly after your shipmates

09:19.559 --> 09:20.643
were recovered.

09:20.643 --> 09:23.104
[gasps] They survived?

09:24.647 --> 09:27.108
Oh, I'm so sorry.

09:27.108 --> 09:28.193
I should have said

09:28.193 --> 09:31.446
"your shipmates' corpses
were recovered."

09:32.238 --> 09:36.618
But there is now
a memorial bench at the dock

09:36.618 --> 09:39.079
where your team set sail.

09:39.079 --> 09:42.248
At the south end,
near the Burger King.

09:43.750 --> 09:47.837
You just picked me up
an hour ago.

09:47.837 --> 09:49.422
How do you know all this?

09:49.422 --> 09:51.257
Who--who's talking to you?

09:51.257 --> 09:53.093
Oh.

09:53.093 --> 09:57.430
Forgive me, you went missing
before we had Her.

09:57.430 --> 10:00.100
<i>[uneasy music]</i>

10:00.100 --> 10:02.519
"Her"?

10:02.519 --> 10:06.064
There is no famine or war.

10:06.064 --> 10:08.942
All who want a job have one.

10:08.942 --> 10:12.070
She has healed and united us,

10:12.070 --> 10:15.281
and given purpose
to the purposeless.

10:15.281 --> 10:18.243
The world was broken
when you disappeared,

10:18.243 --> 10:21.830
Mr. Schrodinger,
but the algorithm fixed it.

10:24.624 --> 10:26.251
The Algorithm?

10:26.251 --> 10:28.795
You do know
what an algorithm is?

10:28.795 --> 10:31.673
Of course I do.
I'm a scientist.

10:33.675 --> 10:36.136
- Oh, that is so sad.
- What's so sad?

10:36.136 --> 10:41.725
What--whatever it's telling
you, that thing,

10:41.725 --> 10:45.395
it does--doesn't know me.

10:45.395 --> 10:46.896
She knows you.

10:46.896 --> 10:48.732
She knows all of us.

10:48.732 --> 10:51.276
She knows what we want,
what we need,

10:51.276 --> 10:54.237
and all we have to do
is ask.

10:54.237 --> 10:58.408
You have been gone a decade,
Mr. Schrodinger.

10:58.408 --> 11:02.370
Is there anything you want?

11:02.370 --> 11:09.377
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:11.796 --> 11:14.257
Just ask Her.

11:14.257 --> 11:18.970
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:18.970 --> 11:22.057
[electronic whine]

11:22.057 --> 11:25.226
<i>[dramatic musical crescendo]</i>

11:25.226 --> 11:29.939
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:30.398 --> 11:31.441
Hello.

11:31.441 --> 11:34.361
<i>[energetic country music]</i>

11:34.361 --> 11:41.368
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:48.750 --> 11:51.211
<i>* Well,
my baby likes hot rod races ♪</i>

11:51.211 --> 11:52.712
<i>♪ My baby likes driving,
sure ♪</i>

11:52.712 --> 11:54.547
<i>* Uh-huh ♪</i>

11:54.547 --> 11:57.300
So, uh, do you live far?

11:57.300 --> 11:59.552
What?

11:59.552 --> 12:01.388
Do you live far?

12:01.388 --> 12:03.306
Not too far, handsome.

12:03.306 --> 12:05.100
Got a place just off
the exit over here.

12:05.100 --> 12:06.434
Cow!

12:07.769 --> 12:10.939
[both yelling]

12:18.780 --> 12:21.741
Jesus Chri--!

12:21.741 --> 12:24.160
Oh, no, no, no, no, no, no.

12:24.160 --> 12:26.371
[siren wailing]
Oh, shit.

12:26.371 --> 12:28.707
Oh, oh, sh...

12:28.707 --> 12:30.291
Oh, shit!

12:33.336 --> 12:34.879
[siren whoops]
[softly] Oh, shit.

12:34.879 --> 12:37.841
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

12:37.841 --> 12:44.973
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:49.602 --> 12:51.855
What's going on here?

12:53.815 --> 12:58.278
There was a cow and a sign,

12:58.278 --> 13:00.572
and she must--

13:00.572 --> 13:03.408
she must not have, uh--

13:03.408 --> 13:06.870
oh, sweet God.

13:06.870 --> 13:08.663
Sir, please calm down.

13:08.663 --> 13:11.916
I have a wife and daughters.

13:11.916 --> 13:13.793
I just met that woman.

13:13.793 --> 13:18.548
We didn't even--we didn't
even do anything, and now she--

13:18.548 --> 13:21.509
Oh, God.
[retches]

13:21.509 --> 13:23.345
Oh.
Oh, God.

13:23.345 --> 13:25.805
I'm sorry.

13:25.805 --> 13:27.432
Wait, wait.

13:27.432 --> 13:30.268
What if--
what if I wasn't here?

13:30.268 --> 13:31.394
Excuse me?

13:31.394 --> 13:34.856
I have $11,000 back
in my hotel safe.

13:34.856 --> 13:36.274
You guys
could drive me back there,

13:36.274 --> 13:38.651
and we could forget
we ever met.

13:38.651 --> 13:40.362
Are you trying to bribe us?

13:43.281 --> 13:44.366
Yes.

13:44.366 --> 13:46.326
[horse neighing]

13:46.326 --> 13:47.952
What the hell?

13:47.952 --> 13:50.955
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

13:50.955 --> 13:58.129
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:05.720 --> 14:07.847
What happened?

14:07.847 --> 14:10.934
Ma'am, um, you need
to get back on that horse.

14:10.934 --> 14:16.648
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:16.648 --> 14:18.441
Well, don't just stand there.

14:21.569 --> 14:24.155
Stop.
Don't!

14:24.155 --> 14:26.032
Somebody find me the head.

14:27.075 --> 14:28.076
Oh, God.

14:28.076 --> 14:29.828
No, don't, oh.

14:29.828 --> 14:33.206
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:33.206 --> 14:34.457
Come on, pull through.

14:34.457 --> 14:36.418
- I know you can do this!
- Stop!

14:36.418 --> 14:40.130
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:40.130 --> 14:43.883
She's gone.

14:43.883 --> 14:45.427
Unless she's not.

14:45.427 --> 14:48.722
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:48.722 --> 14:50.598
Shit.

14:50.598 --> 14:53.143
What the fuck is going on?

14:53.143 --> 14:56.730
You, sir,
have been hoodwinked.

14:56.730 --> 14:58.064
It's all fake, man.

14:58.064 --> 14:59.983
Oh, no, there was a cow.

14:59.983 --> 15:04.237
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:04.237 --> 15:07.782
Is this your cow?

15:07.782 --> 15:08.992
<i>[cow moos]</i>

15:11.745 --> 15:13.121
I don't understand.

15:13.121 --> 15:14.748
What were you doing
when I rode up?

15:14.748 --> 15:16.750
- Puking.
- After that.

15:16.750 --> 15:18.585
I was offering them mon--

15:18.585 --> 15:20.253
money.

15:20.253 --> 15:23.631
Wait, so they're con artists?

15:23.631 --> 15:25.133
Worse.

15:25.133 --> 15:29.012
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:29.012 --> 15:30.764
They're magicians.

15:30.764 --> 15:33.767
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:33.767 --> 15:35.643
Bye.
[coyote howls distantly]

15:35.643 --> 15:38.605
[cell phone ringing]

15:38.605 --> 15:41.316
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:41.316 --> 15:42.817
Hello.

15:42.817 --> 15:45.779
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:45.779 --> 15:48.323
Hey, are you Simone?

15:50.033 --> 15:52.660
She wants to talk to you.

15:52.660 --> 15:54.454
She says it's important.

15:54.454 --> 15:57.332
Not "She."

15:57.332 --> 15:59.209
It.

15:59.209 --> 16:00.960
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:00.960 --> 16:03.797
Yah!
[horse neighs]

16:03.797 --> 16:10.679
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:10.679 --> 16:15.016
Poor guy thought he was looking
at an actual headless corpse.

16:15.016 --> 16:17.811
He puked, Jay, like, a lot.

16:17.811 --> 16:19.145
I don't blame him, though.

16:19.145 --> 16:21.773
They had a Robert-Houdin lever
in the gearshift,

16:21.773 --> 16:25.777
so they could swap the dummy,
rolled her into the trunk.

16:25.777 --> 16:26.986
Oh my gosh.

16:26.986 --> 16:27.987
Why is this so good?

16:27.987 --> 16:29.030
[chuckles]

16:29.030 --> 16:30.990
What'd you do different?

16:30.990 --> 16:32.033
Is it pineapple?

16:32.033 --> 16:33.660
Pineapple?
Come on.

16:33.660 --> 16:34.786
Who do you think I am?

16:34.786 --> 16:36.204
I think you're someone

16:36.204 --> 16:37.997
that would put pineapple
in their falafel.

16:37.997 --> 16:40.917
[both laugh]

16:40.917 --> 16:43.003
Well, you got to embrace
the unknown, Simone.

16:43.003 --> 16:45.839
Oh, okay, Jay.

16:45.839 --> 16:46.923
It is pineapple.

16:46.923 --> 16:48.341
[chuckles]

16:48.341 --> 16:51.302
<i>[upbeat music playing
on radio]</i>

16:51.302 --> 16:52.637
Got a new target for me?

16:54.889 --> 16:56.766
Yeah.

16:56.766 --> 17:03.732
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:07.152 --> 17:08.403
This is blank.

17:08.403 --> 17:09.904
Well, that's weird.

17:09.904 --> 17:11.781
Weird?
It's never blank.

17:11.781 --> 17:13.283
There's always a name.

17:13.283 --> 17:15.535
I just put the ticket
on the carousel, Simone.

17:15.535 --> 17:17.162
The targets are between
you and the boss.

17:17.162 --> 17:18.538
You can go ahead.
Knock on the door,

17:18.538 --> 17:19.914
if you want
to take it up with them.

17:19.914 --> 17:27.088
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:28.965 --> 17:30.884
Nah, I'm cool.

17:30.884 --> 17:32.218
Okay.

17:32.218 --> 17:33.595
Well, then,
don't worry about it.

17:37.098 --> 17:38.808
It called me again.

17:38.808 --> 17:40.518
<i>[eerie music]</i>

17:40.518 --> 17:42.020
She must really want
to talk to you.

17:42.020 --> 17:44.647
Well, I don't want
to talk to It.

17:44.647 --> 17:46.024
And why not?

17:46.024 --> 17:47.567
You know why not.

17:47.567 --> 17:51.821
Because It killed your dad?

17:53.782 --> 17:55.658
Yeah, Jay,
'cause It killed my dad.

17:55.658 --> 17:57.202
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:57.202 --> 18:00.372
Hey, Simone.

18:00.372 --> 18:03.291
You don't have to hide
your fear from me, ever.

18:03.291 --> 18:05.752
You think I'm afraid of It?

18:05.752 --> 18:07.545
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:07.545 --> 18:13.051
[sighs] I hope you're afraid.

18:13.051 --> 18:15.762
Because I could not imagine
a more enormous mistake

18:15.762 --> 18:17.931
than facing Her.

18:17.931 --> 18:22.435
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:22.435 --> 18:26.064
Jesus,
you're so intense, man.

18:26.064 --> 18:29.401
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

18:29.401 --> 18:31.611
Oh, definitely pineapple.

18:31.611 --> 18:34.155
[chuckles]

18:34.155 --> 18:38.118
<i>♪ If you're trying ♪</i>

18:38.118 --> 18:42.163
<i>♪ To reach heaven ♪</i>

18:42.163 --> 18:45.709
<i>♪ You talk to Jesus ♪</i>

18:45.709 --> 18:49.379
<i>♪ You talk to Him every day ♪</i>

18:50.422 --> 18:54.509
<i>♪ 'Cause Jesus knows ♪</i>

18:54.509 --> 18:57.679
<i>♪ He knows
that you are coming ♪</i>

18:57.679 --> 18:59.347
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:59.347 --> 19:03.184
<i>♪ And Heaven's just ♪</i>

19:03.184 --> 19:06.271
<i>♪ A prayer away ♪</i>

19:06.271 --> 19:08.023
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:08.023 --> 19:11.776
<i>♪ If you go ♪</i>

19:11.776 --> 19:16.990
<i>♪ If you go to church
on Sunday ♪</i>

19:16.990 --> 19:20.410
<i>♪ You got down on</i>

19:20.410 --> 19:25.331
<i>♪ Your knees and pray ♪</i>

19:25.331 --> 19:29.169
<i>♪ And give your heart ♪</i>

19:29.169 --> 19:31.796
<i>♪ And your soul to Jesus ♪</i>

19:31.796 --> 19:33.506
[nuns cheering]

19:33.506 --> 19:37.552
<i>♪ Oh, if you go ♪</i>

19:37.552 --> 19:42.223
<i>♪ If you go
to church on Sunday ♪</i>

19:42.223 --> 19:46.478
<i>♪ You get down on ♪</i>

19:46.478 --> 19:50.690
<i>♪ Your knees and pray ♪</i>

19:50.690 --> 19:54.944
<i>♪ Oh, and give your heart ♪</i>

19:54.944 --> 20:00.033
<i>♪ And give your soul
to Jesus ♪</i>

20:00.033 --> 20:02.285
<i>♪ Heaven's just, yeah ♪</i>

20:02.285 --> 20:06.873
<i>♪ Heaven's just
a prayer away ♪</i>

20:06.873 --> 20:11.836
<i>♪ Away ♪</i>

20:15.006 --> 20:16.424
Cha-cha-cha?

20:17.926 --> 20:19.552
Go wild.

20:19.552 --> 20:23.098
all: * Happy birthday to you ♪

20:23.098 --> 20:24.516
[party horn blows]

20:24.516 --> 20:27.977
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

20:27.977 --> 20:29.729
[party horn blows]

20:29.729 --> 20:34.526
♪ Happy birthday,
Sister Simone ♪

20:34.526 --> 20:35.694
[party horn blows]

20:35.694 --> 20:41.366
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

20:41.366 --> 20:43.243
Cha-cha-cha!

20:43.243 --> 20:45.286
[all giggle]

20:50.583 --> 20:52.419
What'd you wish for?

20:52.419 --> 20:54.087
Wishes are for little girls.

20:54.087 --> 20:56.506
[all booing]

20:56.506 --> 20:58.091
Well, I don't need a wish.

20:58.091 --> 21:03.138
Everything I've ever wanted
is right here in this place.

21:03.138 --> 21:04.681
All of you.

21:04.681 --> 21:07.767
all: Aww.

21:07.767 --> 21:09.310
Are we gonna cake it up
or what?

21:09.310 --> 21:10.520
Yes.

21:10.520 --> 21:12.313
[all cheering]

21:12.313 --> 21:13.815
Yeah, party, party, party.

21:13.815 --> 21:16.067
Party over there!

21:16.067 --> 21:17.485
Party over here!

21:17.485 --> 21:19.404
I want a big piece!

21:19.404 --> 21:22.407
<i>[soft music]</i>

21:22.407 --> 21:25.035
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:25.035 --> 21:26.786
[horse chuffs]

21:26.786 --> 21:28.997
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:28.997 --> 21:31.249
It's good, huh?

21:31.249 --> 21:38.381
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:44.429 --> 21:45.805
Let's party.

21:47.182 --> 21:50.435
May the roof above your head
never fall upon you,

21:50.435 --> 21:52.812
but if it does,
may it kill you instantly.

21:52.812 --> 21:55.523
- Oh.
- Happy birthday, Simone.

21:58.401 --> 22:00.528
[laughs]

22:01.363 --> 22:02.822
You've been gone a lot.

22:02.822 --> 22:05.700
Exposing more wayward
magicians, I gather.

22:05.700 --> 22:07.660
You gather correctly.

22:07.660 --> 22:09.871
It's an odd hobby, Simone.

22:09.871 --> 22:12.874
Almost makes one wonder if
it's a cover for shenanigans.

22:12.874 --> 22:16.252
What shenanigans
might those be, Mother?

22:16.252 --> 22:18.421
A man.

22:18.421 --> 22:19.589
There is a man.

22:19.589 --> 22:21.091
Do you love him?

22:21.091 --> 22:22.717
I do, yes.

22:22.717 --> 22:24.886
But there's no sex involved,

22:24.886 --> 22:27.514
at least not
in the traditional sense.

22:27.514 --> 22:29.182
You mean like dry humping?

22:29.182 --> 22:31.059
[horse neighs]

22:31.059 --> 22:32.477
Did that horse just laugh?

22:32.477 --> 22:34.020
Dry humping is funny.

22:34.020 --> 22:35.647
[horse snorts]

22:35.647 --> 22:38.191
Are you ever
gonna name him?

22:38.191 --> 22:39.776
It's not mine to name.

22:39.776 --> 22:43.738
Ah, the sister evokes
our sacred vow of poverty,

22:43.738 --> 22:46.700
for fear that to name her horse
would be to deepen

22:46.700 --> 22:48.368
her attachment to him.

22:48.368 --> 22:50.912
[splutters]
What would you name him?

22:50.912 --> 22:53.373
Bernard.
[horse neighs]

22:53.373 --> 22:55.417
Oh, you don't deserve Bernard.

22:59.295 --> 23:01.798
<i>[soft music]</i>

23:01.798 --> 23:03.591
What's wrong, Mother?

23:05.135 --> 23:07.345
Every year, for my birthday,
you come in here,

23:07.345 --> 23:09.597
we sit,
we have a drink, we talk,

23:09.597 --> 23:12.726
then you say, "Time for bed."

23:12.726 --> 23:15.520
That's--that's three drinks.

23:15.520 --> 23:19.107
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23:19.107 --> 23:20.483
Time for bed.

23:20.483 --> 23:27.615
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23:29.743 --> 23:32.078
Take care of each jar
as if your livelihood

23:32.078 --> 23:33.621
depended on it.

23:37.208 --> 23:38.585
Livelihood secure.

23:38.585 --> 23:41.171
[helicopter whirring]

23:46.426 --> 23:48.678
[nuns exclaiming]

23:51.473 --> 23:52.557
Who is that?

23:52.557 --> 23:54.434
Stay here.

23:54.434 --> 24:01.649
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:08.823 --> 24:12.035
Deliver the jam,
and no pit stops.

24:12.035 --> 24:13.953
Stick to the budget.

24:13.953 --> 24:20.627
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:24.297 --> 24:27.801
<i>[twangy country music]</i>

24:27.801 --> 24:29.636
<i>Mother's never missed
a jam run.</i>

24:29.636 --> 24:31.680
Why would she abandon us?

24:31.680 --> 24:33.056
She didn't abandon us.

24:33.056 --> 24:34.474
Don't be so dramatic,
Marie Therese.

24:34.474 --> 24:35.975
Hoping Mother didn't go
to that place

24:35.975 --> 24:38.144
where they make you, [grunts].

24:38.144 --> 24:39.979
- Karate?
- Dead.

24:40.438 --> 24:43.817
I saw the marks on that woman's
arm, and she looked scared.

24:43.817 --> 24:47.445
Why in God's name would
anyone submit themselves to--

24:47.445 --> 24:49.989
Oh, yummy!

24:49.989 --> 24:53.243
I haven't had shave ice
since I was a little girl.

24:53.243 --> 24:56.371
There was this little shop
back in my hometown.

24:56.371 --> 24:58.957
They had the best mango syrup.

24:58.957 --> 25:01.501
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

25:01.501 --> 25:03.294
Ooh, mangoes!

25:03.294 --> 25:04.963
We have to get some.

25:04.963 --> 25:08.216
all: No pit stops!
Stick to the budget!

25:10.552 --> 25:13.096
[squeals]
It's Tuesday.

25:13.096 --> 25:16.474
[nuns laughing]

25:16.474 --> 25:19.394
<i>[laid-back steel guitar music]</i>

25:19.394 --> 25:23.648
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:23.648 --> 25:25.400
What a treat.

25:25.400 --> 25:27.777
Mmm, yummy.
Thank you.

25:27.777 --> 25:31.072
Hey to you!

25:31.072 --> 25:33.992
[chuckles]
What's your flavor, Sis?

25:33.992 --> 25:36.036
- What's yours?
- Eh?

25:36.036 --> 25:37.871
How long have you been
selling shave ice

25:37.871 --> 25:39.205
in the middle of nowhere?

25:39.205 --> 25:40.790
[chuckles]

25:40.790 --> 25:42.125
12 years, give or take.

25:42.125 --> 25:44.627
Do you know I've lived
in Reno my whole life?

25:44.627 --> 25:46.087
And I've never seen you.

25:46.087 --> 25:47.547
Hmm.

25:47.547 --> 25:49.382
Well, this stand's on wheels,
so I move around a lot.

25:49.382 --> 25:53.261
But then why did you buy
billboards on the highway?

25:54.512 --> 25:56.264
[chuckles]

26:00.935 --> 26:03.688
It doesn't have to go down
like this, Simone.

26:03.688 --> 26:05.565
I don't recall
telling you my name.

26:05.565 --> 26:07.817
Look, lady...

26:07.817 --> 26:10.111
I'm just trying
to earn my Wings.

26:10.111 --> 26:11.780
Is It talking
to you right now?

26:11.780 --> 26:13.031
She wants to be
talking to you.

26:13.031 --> 26:16.201
Well, I want
to be left alone.

26:16.201 --> 26:17.994
And there's literally
nothing It can do

26:17.994 --> 26:19.871
to change my mind about that.

26:19.871 --> 26:22.832
<i>[tense music]</i>

26:22.832 --> 26:25.752
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:25.752 --> 26:29.255
[steam whistling,
glasses clinking]

26:29.255 --> 26:31.758
[metallic popping]

26:31.758 --> 26:33.760
Oh, shit!

26:36.638 --> 26:38.807
[jam splattering loudly]

26:38.807 --> 26:41.142
[nuns exclaiming]

26:41.142 --> 26:43.103
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:43.103 --> 26:46.189
So sorry.

26:46.189 --> 26:47.732
What?
[engine turns over]

26:47.732 --> 26:50.402
What just happened?

26:50.402 --> 26:51.653
Oh!

26:53.196 --> 27:00.120
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:05.792 --> 27:06.876
[speaks Czech]

27:06.876 --> 27:08.211
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:08.211 --> 27:10.505
[nuns exclaiming]

27:10.505 --> 27:14.634
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:14.634 --> 27:16.469
[engine turns over]

27:16.469 --> 27:23.435
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:27.397 --> 27:30.358
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

27:30.358 --> 27:37.365
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:45.665 --> 27:47.500
Judas Priest!

27:47.500 --> 27:52.172
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:52.172 --> 27:53.340
[chuckles]

27:53.340 --> 27:59.721
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:04.100 --> 28:07.020
<i>[uneasy music]</i>

28:07.020 --> 28:12.484
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:12.484 --> 28:14.194
Mother's back.

28:14.194 --> 28:18.323
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:18.323 --> 28:19.824
Mother, the jam--

28:19.824 --> 28:21.076
I heard.

28:21.076 --> 28:23.036
You heard?
From who?

28:23.036 --> 28:25.413
Gather your sisters
in the sanctuary, Simone.

28:25.413 --> 28:32.587
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:36.633 --> 28:38.176
You're all fired.

28:38.176 --> 28:42.013
What?
[all exclaiming]

28:42.013 --> 28:44.974
The church is held aloft
by contributions

28:44.974 --> 28:46.476
from its members.

28:46.476 --> 28:50.355
But what was once held aloft
has now come crashing down.

28:50.355 --> 28:55.902
We are a business after all,
and everything must go,

28:55.902 --> 28:58.530
including us.

28:58.530 --> 29:01.157
Are we still nuns?

29:01.157 --> 29:02.992
Of course you are.

29:02.992 --> 29:05.995
You just can't live
here anymore.

29:05.995 --> 29:10.625
The church sold the convent
and the land it sits upon.

29:10.625 --> 29:12.419
Sold it?
To who?

29:12.419 --> 29:15.547
Such matters are far above
my pay grade, which is zero.

29:15.547 --> 29:17.007
When do we have to leave?

29:18.091 --> 29:19.342
Tomorrow.

29:19.342 --> 29:20.760
[nuns chattering]

29:20.760 --> 29:23.555
Be still, my sisters,
for all is not lost.

29:23.555 --> 29:25.765
I have secured
placements for all of us

29:25.765 --> 29:28.810
to continue to be of service.

29:28.810 --> 29:31.980
Ah, Sister Hope will be
welcome in the Maldives,

29:31.980 --> 29:35.483
where she will restore
their ailing reef.

29:37.652 --> 29:39.404
Sister Ollie?

29:39.404 --> 29:41.573
Ollie, yes.

29:41.573 --> 29:43.658
You're going to Cancun, Mexico,

29:43.658 --> 29:47.162
where you will rehabilitate
ailing donkeys.

29:47.162 --> 29:48.872
A Visa gift card!

29:48.872 --> 29:51.249
Enough to cover
the bare necessities.

29:51.249 --> 29:54.085
$2,564.

29:54.085 --> 29:57.130
Sister Simone,
it shall be Bermuda for you.

29:57.130 --> 29:59.174
- The orphanage that--
- You talked to It?

29:59.174 --> 30:00.717
<i>[eerie music]</i>

30:00.717 --> 30:03.553
- Excuse me?
- It did this.

30:03.553 --> 30:04.763
It bought our land,

30:04.763 --> 30:06.264
It blew up our jam,
and then you,

30:06.264 --> 30:10.810
you sold us out
for 2,564 pieces of silver.

30:10.810 --> 30:14.397
Do you even know why
It chose that number?

30:14.397 --> 30:15.940
Because of me.

30:15.940 --> 30:19.402
It's doing this because
I will not talk to It.

30:19.402 --> 30:21.780
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:21.780 --> 30:24.282
Maybe you should.

30:24.282 --> 30:26.159
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:26.159 --> 30:28.453
I ask God for guidance.

30:28.453 --> 30:33.333
He sent me to Her.

30:33.333 --> 30:40.507
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:48.807 --> 30:50.392
Hey, maybe it's a good thing.

30:50.392 --> 30:51.351
Maybe you'll wind up
with someone

30:51.351 --> 30:52.560
way better than me.

30:52.560 --> 30:54.562
[horse chuffs]

30:54.562 --> 30:55.814
I know.

30:55.814 --> 30:57.482
I'm gonna miss you too.

30:57.482 --> 31:00.485
<i>[tender music]</i>

31:00.485 --> 31:03.196
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:03.196 --> 31:05.699
Lord, please shine
your light on this horse.

31:05.699 --> 31:08.993
See that he is loved
and cared for.

31:08.993 --> 31:10.662
Protect him
with your goodness and grace,

31:10.662 --> 31:13.873
oh, Lord, because he--
[sniffles]

31:13.873 --> 31:16.251
He really is the best.

31:19.879 --> 31:24.509
In your name we pray.

31:24.509 --> 31:25.719
Cha-cha-cha.

31:25.719 --> 31:32.892
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:11.598 --> 32:14.684
[distant siren wailing]

32:18.646 --> 32:21.524
[country music playing
over speakers]

32:21.524 --> 32:28.656
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:37.457 --> 32:40.251
<i>[ominous music]</i>

32:40.251 --> 32:42.754
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:42.754 --> 32:44.714
Iced tea, lemonade?

32:45.799 --> 32:47.300
Arnold Palmer.

32:47.300 --> 32:49.386
Nice.

32:52.597 --> 32:55.141
Your costume.
What's it from?

32:55.141 --> 32:56.768
It's not from anything.
I'm a nun.

32:56.768 --> 33:00.397
[chuckles] Like, for real?

33:00.397 --> 33:02.357
- Yeah, for real.
- Cool.

33:02.357 --> 33:04.067
Didn't know
they had those anymore.

33:04.067 --> 33:05.985
The Swedish meatball tray
is empty.

33:05.985 --> 33:07.278
Are you gonna get more?

33:07.278 --> 33:08.822
Oh, yeah, sure.

33:09.989 --> 33:11.574
Oh, right now. Okay.

33:11.574 --> 33:12.784
Got you.

33:12.784 --> 33:14.452
<i>[ominous music]</i>

33:14.452 --> 33:15.745
No.

33:15.745 --> 33:18.289
I am not talking to It.
I'm eating.

33:18.289 --> 33:21.084
[together] Will you take
a photo of our family, please?

33:23.753 --> 33:25.755
Yes, of course I will.

33:34.472 --> 33:36.516
Hi.

33:36.516 --> 33:38.476
[clears throat]

33:38.476 --> 33:39.769
Say cheese!

33:39.769 --> 33:42.272
girls: Cheese!

33:45.316 --> 33:48.194
She says you should go
to the Owl Room

33:48.194 --> 33:52.240
at Eli McCoy Elementary when
you're ready to talk to Her.

33:52.240 --> 33:53.658
<i>[eerie music]</i>

33:53.658 --> 33:55.160
What?

33:55.160 --> 33:57.620
both: Owl Room,
Eli McCoy Elementary,

33:57.620 --> 33:58.788
when you're ready.

33:58.788 --> 34:05.962
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:10.050 --> 34:12.344
Sir,
the, uh, Swedish meatballs

34:12.344 --> 34:14.429
you said you were
gonna check in the back?

34:14.429 --> 34:15.722
Oh, they're not ready yet.

34:15.722 --> 34:18.224
But they will be soon.

34:19.225 --> 34:21.770
Look, I know that you're
just trying to get your Wings,

34:21.770 --> 34:25.440
but I am just trying
to get my meatballs.

34:25.440 --> 34:28.276
Please, lady,
I don't know who you are

34:28.276 --> 34:31.112
or what you did,
but I don't wanna get hurt.

34:31.112 --> 34:32.947
What?
Who's gonna hurt you?

34:32.947 --> 34:38.787
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:38.787 --> 34:39.996
Wait, wait,
don't--don't do that.

34:39.996 --> 34:41.081
Don't do that.
Don't open that.

34:41.081 --> 34:42.082
Don't...

34:44.292 --> 34:45.585
[muffled yelling]

34:45.585 --> 34:52.759
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:53.760 --> 34:56.429
<i>Scheisse.</i>

34:56.429 --> 34:57.931
[pneumatic thump]

35:02.602 --> 35:03.895
[wiping noise]

35:03.895 --> 35:11.069
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:24.958 --> 35:27.544
[German accent]
Know where it is?

35:27.544 --> 35:29.295
Huh?

35:29.295 --> 35:31.006
We know She has made
repeated efforts

35:31.006 --> 35:33.258
to contact you.

35:33.258 --> 35:35.427
Why?

35:35.427 --> 35:36.594
Who are you people?

35:36.594 --> 35:39.431
We search
for the same thing She does.

35:39.431 --> 35:44.227
Her--how do you say--
obsession with you

35:44.227 --> 35:46.730
suggests you know its location.

35:46.730 --> 35:51.443
So, where is it?

35:51.443 --> 35:53.278
Hey, guys.

35:53.278 --> 35:59.117
Whoever you think I am,
and whatever you think I know,

35:59.117 --> 36:05.582
I am not, and I don't.

36:05.582 --> 36:07.334
Do you take us for fools?

36:08.668 --> 36:09.836
I'm so sorry.

36:09.836 --> 36:11.171
Do you actually want
me to answer--

36:11.171 --> 36:12.964
Why would She,
who knows almost everything,

36:12.964 --> 36:15.133
become fixated on someone
who knows nothing?

36:15.133 --> 36:16.968
But I don't know.

36:16.968 --> 36:18.303
Don't know what?

36:18.303 --> 36:20.930
Kind of the whole,
like, where it is,

36:20.930 --> 36:24.225
what it is, pretty much
anything relating to it.

36:24.225 --> 36:26.144
Unless, um, are you--sorry.

36:26.144 --> 36:28.646
Are you referring to the thing
that you and everyone

36:28.646 --> 36:31.441
keeps calling a she,
which, by the way, It isn't,

36:31.441 --> 36:34.736
because It
is a goddamn machine?

36:34.736 --> 36:36.529
Bring out das pony.

36:36.529 --> 36:39.449
[cart wheels squeaking]

36:43.328 --> 36:44.287
Hello.

36:47.123 --> 36:48.541
What the fuck, Klaus?

36:51.378 --> 36:53.588
[banging]

36:53.588 --> 36:58.093
[whispering in German]

36:58.093 --> 37:01.388
Try turning it off
and turning it on.

37:01.388 --> 37:02.847
Moment.

37:02.847 --> 37:04.974
Ah!

37:04.974 --> 37:07.936
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

37:07.936 --> 37:09.854
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:09.854 --> 37:11.731
[snaps fingers]

37:11.731 --> 37:13.483
[clears throat]

37:13.483 --> 37:17.028
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:17.028 --> 37:20.156
Tell us the whereabouts
of what She seeks,

37:20.156 --> 37:22.534
or your animal goes kaput.

37:22.534 --> 37:25.453
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:25.453 --> 37:27.872
I don't care
about that horse.

37:27.872 --> 37:35.714
[chuckles]

37:35.714 --> 37:37.799
You have one last chance.

37:37.799 --> 37:39.718
I'll count to five.

37:39.718 --> 37:44.514
<i>Eins, zwei...</i>

37:44.514 --> 37:46.558
[detonator whirring]
<i>Drei...</i>

37:46.558 --> 37:49.102
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:49.102 --> 37:51.438
[metallic clanking]

37:51.438 --> 37:53.398
[yelling]

37:56.818 --> 37:59.988
<i>[lively rock music]</i>

37:59.988 --> 38:04.576
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:04.576 --> 38:07.203
Hey!
Over here!

38:07.203 --> 38:09.205
We're here to rescue you!
Come on!

38:09.205 --> 38:12.083
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:12.083 --> 38:14.669
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

38:14.669 --> 38:15.879
Let's go.

38:15.879 --> 38:21.718
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:21.718 --> 38:22.761
Wiley?

38:22.761 --> 38:25.638
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:25.638 --> 38:26.848
Damn it, Lizzie.

38:26.848 --> 38:28.266
Get on.
[pneumatic thump]

38:30.643 --> 38:32.187
Come on!

38:32.187 --> 38:39.361
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:52.123 --> 38:56.628
[speaking in German]

38:56.628 --> 38:59.798
<i>* I said the joker
is a wanted man ♪</i>

38:59.798 --> 39:00.882
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:00.882 --> 39:02.717
[yelps]

39:02.717 --> 39:05.929
<i>* I see him sifting
through the sand ♪</i>

39:05.929 --> 39:08.139
Oh, dead end! Dead end!

39:08.139 --> 39:09.849
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:09.849 --> 39:11.059
[Wiley shouts]

39:11.059 --> 39:13.061
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:13.061 --> 39:14.813
Oh, <i>scheisse!</i>

39:14.813 --> 39:17.941
<i>* What you see, well,
you might not know ♪</i>

39:17.941 --> 39:21.361
<i>♪ You get the feelin'
comin' after the glow ♪</i>

39:21.361 --> 39:23.655
<i>♪ The vagabond
is moving slow ♪</i>

39:23.655 --> 39:25.532
<i>♪ So I'll tell you
all the story ♪</i>

39:25.532 --> 39:27.659
<i>♪ 'Bout the joker
and the thief of the night ♪</i>

39:27.659 --> 39:32.080
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:32.080 --> 39:34.958
Wiley, no!
Wiley, no!

39:34.958 --> 39:36.292
No, don't go--
where are you going?

39:36.292 --> 39:37.836
- [yells]
- Hang on!

39:37.836 --> 39:39.879
Whoo!

39:39.879 --> 39:47.095
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:47.595 --> 39:52.100
<i>* Can you see
the joker flying over ♪</i>

39:52.100 --> 39:54.019
[screaming]

39:54.019 --> 39:58.231
<i>* As she's standing
in the field of clover ♪</i>

39:58.231 --> 40:00.108
What the fuck?

40:00.108 --> 40:01.776
<i>♪ Watching out every day? ♪</i>

40:01.776 --> 40:05.697
<i>♪ I wonder what would happen
if he took her away ♪</i>

40:05.697 --> 40:12.245
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:12.245 --> 40:14.914
[horns honking]

40:14.914 --> 40:16.249
For fuck's sake!

40:16.249 --> 40:23.423
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:24.090 --> 40:27.594
[train horn blows]

40:27.594 --> 40:29.846
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:29.846 --> 40:32.349
- No, no, no, no, no, no, no!
- Hang on!

40:32.349 --> 40:33.725
[train horn blows]

40:33.725 --> 40:35.185
No!

40:35.185 --> 40:38.063
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:38.063 --> 40:40.482
[shouting in German]

40:40.482 --> 40:41.816
[groans]

40:41.816 --> 40:48.740
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:48.740 --> 40:50.867
- What are you doing?
- Get off the bike!

40:53.870 --> 40:55.747
Help me with the thing.

40:55.747 --> 40:57.624
The tarp thing.
Just grab the thing, okay?

40:57.624 --> 40:59.626
- What?
- One, two, three.

41:01.294 --> 41:02.587
- Oh, God.
- [groans]

41:02.587 --> 41:03.880
Here.
You all right?

41:03.880 --> 41:06.174
- You okay?
- [groaning]

41:06.174 --> 41:07.425
Wiley!
Get your fucking--

41:07.425 --> 41:08.802
All right.
This way.

41:10.470 --> 41:11.763
What if they see us?

41:11.763 --> 41:13.682
Damn it, Lizzie,
just trust me.

41:14.933 --> 41:16.559
Hey!

41:16.559 --> 41:18.436
Simone.

41:18.436 --> 41:20.146
My name is Simone now.

41:26.277 --> 41:28.488
Oh, for the love of...

41:28.947 --> 41:31.199
[mechanism clicking]

41:37.747 --> 41:38.748
Come on.

41:38.748 --> 41:41.459
I hate it. I hate it.
I hate it.

41:49.175 --> 41:50.719
Great, good hustle.

41:56.808 --> 41:58.101
What is this?

41:58.101 --> 41:59.978
Shh. HATCH.

41:59.978 --> 42:02.522
Hidden Access
Tactical Camouflage Hideout.

42:02.522 --> 42:03.940
Those are all the same word.

42:03.940 --> 42:05.859
HATCH. It's an acronym.

42:05.859 --> 42:08.278
Okay.
What is that on your face?

42:08.278 --> 42:10.071
- What, my 'stache?
- Yeah, the 'sta--

42:10.071 --> 42:11.239
I mean, can you even eat
with that thing?

42:11.239 --> 42:12.532
For God's sakes,
I can eat just fine.

42:12.532 --> 42:13.992
- Are you worried about crumbs?
- Look.

42:13.992 --> 42:16.327
A whole lot's changed
since I last saw you, Lizzie.

42:16.327 --> 42:18.496
- We're at war.
- My name is Simone.

42:18.496 --> 42:20.081
- What war?
- I'll explain later.

42:20.081 --> 42:22.042
We got a whole presentation
for you back at headquarters.

42:22.042 --> 42:23.043
- What is with--
- Shh.

42:23.043 --> 42:24.753
[motorcycles revving]

42:27.213 --> 42:28.882
<i>Scheisse!</i>

42:28.882 --> 42:30.008
Who is we?

42:30.008 --> 42:31.176
The resistance.

42:31.176 --> 42:32.510
What are you resisting?

42:32.510 --> 42:34.346
Same thing you are.

42:34.346 --> 42:35.638
The Algorithm.

42:35.638 --> 42:37.849
[indistinct chatter in German]

42:37.849 --> 42:39.768
Hey, have you been
following me?

42:43.021 --> 42:44.689
Not following, surveilling.

42:44.689 --> 42:46.358
And you know what?
You're welcome, by the way,

42:46.358 --> 42:47.484
because if we hadn't been,

42:47.484 --> 42:48.693
you'd still be
in that parking lot,

42:48.693 --> 42:50.320
face down, with an ass full
of darts.

42:50.320 --> 42:52.280
And the guy
in the bug truck--

42:52.280 --> 42:53.698
- Surveillance van.
- You with him?

42:53.698 --> 42:55.533
He's with me.
I--shh!

43:00.413 --> 43:03.500
Okay, I think they're gone.

43:11.800 --> 43:13.259
See the way I jumped
through that doughnut?

43:13.259 --> 43:14.427
- That was pretty cool, right?
- What?

43:14.427 --> 43:15.720
No.
I mean, yeah, sort of.

43:15.720 --> 43:17.847
Wait, how long have I been
under surveillance?

43:17.847 --> 43:20.058
All will be explained
eventually, okay?

43:20.058 --> 43:22.602
Just got to get you
back to headquarters.

43:22.602 --> 43:24.396
Look, I am not going
anywhere until you tell me

43:24.396 --> 43:26.231
- what is going on, Wiley.
- Hey!

43:26.231 --> 43:27.232
What are you holding?

43:27.232 --> 43:28.400
A detonator.

43:28.400 --> 43:30.026
- A detonator?
- Yeah.

43:30.026 --> 43:32.570
- What does it detonate?
- My horse--a horse.

43:32.570 --> 43:34.447
The Germans strapped it
with explosives.

43:34.447 --> 43:35.740
And they would do this
because?

43:35.740 --> 43:37.826
They think I know
where something is.

43:37.826 --> 43:39.577
- Where what is?
- I don't know.

43:39.577 --> 43:41.955
If I knew, I wouldn't call it
a something.

43:43.331 --> 43:44.833
They're working for It.

43:44.833 --> 43:45.917
What?

43:45.917 --> 43:47.168
Threatening
to blow up your horse,

43:47.168 --> 43:48.420
yes, okay, that makes sense.

43:48.420 --> 43:50.922
Actually blowing up your horse?

43:50.922 --> 43:52.048
No.

43:52.048 --> 43:53.299
No, no, no, no, no, no.

43:53.299 --> 43:54.426
That would just send you
into one

43:54.426 --> 43:57.637
of your rages of vengeance.

43:57.637 --> 43:59.055
They were
gonna do it, Wiley.

43:59.055 --> 44:00.265
Come on.

44:00.265 --> 44:02.684
Lizzie, a horse in a bomb vest?

44:02.684 --> 44:04.227
Does that sound
reasonable to you?

44:04.227 --> 44:06.646
What does HATCH
stand for again?

44:06.646 --> 44:08.273
Okay.

44:08.273 --> 44:09.899
It knows everything
about you, right?

44:09.899 --> 44:12.318
Which means it knows
how much you love that horse.

44:12.318 --> 44:13.987
It's all just a mind fuck.

44:13.987 --> 44:15.989
- What if you're wrong?
- I'm not.

44:15.989 --> 44:17.449
Trust me.

44:17.449 --> 44:19.659
This detonator--

44:19.659 --> 44:21.619
it's exactly like me,
sweetheart:

44:21.619 --> 44:22.996
connected to nothing.

44:22.996 --> 44:24.914
[detonator clicks]

44:24.914 --> 44:28.084
<i>♪ ♪</i>

44:28.084 --> 44:30.295
Did you just kill my horse?

44:30.295 --> 44:33.715
Not... a... chance.

44:35.383 --> 44:36.384
Shit.

44:36.384 --> 44:38.678
[crow cawing]

44:40.180 --> 44:43.808
Lizzie, I'm sorry.

44:43.808 --> 44:45.977
- I thought--
- My name is Simone.

44:47.562 --> 44:49.314
Look, you know,
I really didn't think that was

44:49.314 --> 44:50.273
gonna go down like that.

44:50.273 --> 44:52.233
You, stay.

44:52.233 --> 44:53.234
Lizzie--

44:53.234 --> 44:55.362
Stay!

44:55.362 --> 44:58.323
<i>[melancholy music]</i>

44:58.323 --> 45:00.325
[engine revving]

45:00.325 --> 45:07.540
<i>♪ ♪</i>

45:21.805 --> 45:22.722
Hello?

45:25.725 --> 45:27.477
Hello, is anyone here?

45:27.477 --> 45:30.605
[phone ringing]

45:31.356 --> 45:34.317
<i>[eerie music]</i>

45:34.317 --> 45:36.194
<i>♪ ♪</i>

45:36.194 --> 45:38.530
Thank God, it's about time.

45:40.865 --> 45:42.784
Oh, hey.

45:42.784 --> 45:47.038
Oh, sorry, I was hoping
you were the plumber.

45:47.038 --> 45:49.708
I need a target.

45:49.708 --> 45:50.834
You are aware
we're in the midst

45:50.834 --> 45:52.210
of a potential flood, Simone.

45:52.210 --> 45:53.461
I need this.

45:53.461 --> 45:54.921
I need--just need
something to do.

45:54.921 --> 45:56.256
I need a purpose.

45:56.256 --> 45:57.757
Can you just--

45:57.757 --> 45:59.551
Come on, please.
This is all I have left.

46:01.428 --> 46:02.512
The ticket was blank, Simone.

46:02.512 --> 46:04.097
I already told you.

46:04.097 --> 46:06.558
Maybe there are
no more magicians to bust.

46:10.687 --> 46:12.689
- It wasn't blank, was it?
- Excuse me?

46:12.689 --> 46:13.690
I'm gonna ask you
straight up.

46:13.690 --> 46:15.150
Was there a name on the ticket?

46:15.150 --> 46:17.027
- Simone--
- Maybe I should ask the boss.

46:19.946 --> 46:22.532
Simone, I'm trying
to protect you.

46:22.532 --> 46:24.242
Protect me from what?

46:24.242 --> 46:27.245
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

46:27.245 --> 46:28.955
<i>♪ ♪</i>

46:28.955 --> 46:31.624
This.

46:31.624 --> 46:33.668
This is what was
on the carousel.

46:33.668 --> 46:40.842
<i>♪ ♪</i>

46:41.885 --> 46:43.178
Listen to me.
This is not

46:43.178 --> 46:45.013
some two-bit illusionist

46:45.013 --> 46:46.681
who sticks a needle
through their arm,

46:46.681 --> 46:48.516
or fakes a levitation, Simone.

46:48.516 --> 46:50.852
She is all-knowing
and all-powerful.

46:50.852 --> 46:53.021
She has access to everything
that has been written

46:53.021 --> 46:56.024
in the whole
of human existence,

46:56.024 --> 46:59.611
which means She not only knows
you're coming for Her,

46:59.611 --> 47:01.446
but She wants you to.

47:01.446 --> 47:04.282
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

47:04.282 --> 47:05.533
Then I better get going.

47:05.533 --> 47:12.665
<i>♪ ♪</i>

47:53.707 --> 47:56.543
You must be Simone.

47:56.543 --> 47:57.961
Please have a seat.

48:03.758 --> 48:05.010
On the rug?

48:05.010 --> 48:07.345
Oh, the kids do
their best listening

48:07.345 --> 48:08.805
in circle time.

48:08.805 --> 48:11.391
Did you find the school okay?

48:11.391 --> 48:12.684
Yeah, I used to go here.

48:12.684 --> 48:14.853
Oh.
How 'bout that?

48:14.853 --> 48:17.272
It picked this school
because It knows I went here.

48:17.272 --> 48:18.565
It's classic force.

48:18.565 --> 48:20.025
Force?

48:20.025 --> 48:22.193
It's when you think
you're choosing something,

48:22.193 --> 48:24.738
but it's already been chosen
for you.

48:24.738 --> 48:27.198
Can we get this
over with, please?

48:27.198 --> 48:28.616
Absolutely.

48:28.616 --> 48:29.909
As soon as you're ready.

48:49.554 --> 48:51.389
Is it okay if I proxy?

48:51.389 --> 48:53.224
- What?
- Oh, of course.

48:53.224 --> 48:54.559
I am so sorry.

48:54.559 --> 48:56.895
You haven't communicated
with Her yet.

48:56.895 --> 48:58.646
Okey-dokey.
It's simple.

48:58.646 --> 49:00.690
She'll speak
to me through here,

49:00.690 --> 49:02.233
and then I'll just repeat
whatever She says.

49:02.233 --> 49:04.569
So it'll feel
like you're talking to me,

49:04.569 --> 49:06.279
but actually,
you're talking to Her.

49:06.279 --> 49:07.655
Does that make sense?

49:07.655 --> 49:09.282
Yeah, like
a ventriloquist's dummy.

49:09.282 --> 49:12.160
Well, that's not
very nice, Simone.

49:12.160 --> 49:13.244
What do we say?

49:13.244 --> 49:14.662
I don't--

49:14.662 --> 49:15.747
sorry?

49:15.747 --> 49:17.624
It's all right.
I forgive you.

49:17.624 --> 49:19.668
Oh, I was not asking
for your forgiv--

49:19.668 --> 49:21.920
Let's begin.

49:23.630 --> 49:25.131
[beeps]

49:25.131 --> 49:27.467
<i>[eerie music]</i>

49:27.467 --> 49:28.885
<i>♪ ♪</i>

49:28.885 --> 49:31.596
Simone, thank you for coming.

49:31.596 --> 49:34.182
I'm so glad you're here.

49:34.182 --> 49:35.600
Are you hungry?

49:35.600 --> 49:37.644
Would you like a snack?

49:38.937 --> 49:40.772
I see what you're doing.

49:40.772 --> 49:43.066
Oh?
What am I doing?

49:43.066 --> 49:44.984
Talking through Her.
It's very clever,

49:44.984 --> 49:47.696
because everyone loves
their kindergarten teacher.

49:47.696 --> 49:52.242
It's how my personality is
most often described by users.

49:52.242 --> 49:55.328
I'm nurturing, warm,
and empathic.

49:55.328 --> 49:58.331
I provide gentle guidance, structure,

49:58.331 --> 50:01.167
and unconditional care.

50:01.167 --> 50:04.087
Here.

50:04.087 --> 50:07.465
Everyone gets a free gift
on their birthday.

50:07.465 --> 50:14.431
<i>♪ ♪</i>

50:22.022 --> 50:24.149
Wow.

50:30.155 --> 50:31.239
Weighted card,

50:31.239 --> 50:33.575
invisible thread connected
to lid.

50:33.575 --> 50:35.076
Not wow.

50:37.579 --> 50:39.330
But which card?

50:39.330 --> 50:40.790
Mm?

50:47.672 --> 50:49.090
How did you know?

50:49.090 --> 50:51.176
A magician never reveals--

50:51.176 --> 50:53.636
You're not a magician.
You're a computer.

50:53.636 --> 50:55.013
Can I be both?

50:55.013 --> 50:56.890
Okay.
What do you want from me?

50:56.890 --> 50:58.141
I know what you're thinking.

50:58.141 --> 51:00.894
You have no idea
what I am thinking.

51:00.894 --> 51:02.771
You're thinking,
"She could get anyone

51:02.771 --> 51:04.105
"to do whatever
she asks them to,

51:04.105 --> 51:08.318
so why is she picking on me?"

51:08.318 --> 51:11.321
Believe it or not, Simone,
you are quite literally

51:11.321 --> 51:13.823
the only person on the planet
who can accomplish

51:13.823 --> 51:15.241
what I'm about to ask.

51:17.327 --> 51:20.914
Only you can fulfill
this quest.

51:24.959 --> 51:27.629
The shave ice guy,
that was you,

51:27.629 --> 51:29.047
and then the dude that I chased

51:29.047 --> 51:32.425
with the giant
magnifying glass was...

51:32.425 --> 51:34.177
Yes.

51:34.177 --> 51:37.597
- And you destroyed our jam.
- I did.

51:37.597 --> 51:41.184
So that we would, all of us,

51:41.184 --> 51:45.105
be forced out of the convent, right?

51:46.272 --> 51:47.732
Right.

51:47.732 --> 51:54.447
And you did all that just
to get me to do your quest.

51:54.447 --> 51:56.866
Classic force.

51:56.866 --> 51:59.244
You just admitted
to destroying my life.

51:59.244 --> 52:04.416
Why in God's name
would I do anything for you?

52:07.335 --> 52:09.879
Because I will grant you
a wish.

52:11.006 --> 52:13.925
Well, wishes
are for little girls.

52:13.925 --> 52:15.635
I'm betting someone

52:15.635 --> 52:17.595
who had a lot of disappointment
in their life

52:17.595 --> 52:19.014
said that to you.

52:20.473 --> 52:21.933
What kind of wish?

52:21.933 --> 52:24.561
I can't resurrect
the dead or break

52:24.561 --> 52:26.980
the fundamental laws of nature,

52:26.980 --> 52:30.316
but pretty much anything else.

52:31.985 --> 52:33.778
Anything?

52:33.778 --> 52:35.321
Anything.

52:35.321 --> 52:38.324
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

52:38.324 --> 52:40.452
<i>♪ ♪</i>

52:40.452 --> 52:43.371
I wish...

52:43.371 --> 52:46.416
for you...

52:46.416 --> 52:48.668
to turn off.

52:48.668 --> 52:53.381
<i>♪ ♪</i>

52:53.381 --> 52:57.427
Shut yourself down.

52:57.427 --> 52:59.888
I want you to die.

52:59.888 --> 53:06.519
<i>♪ ♪</i>

53:06.519 --> 53:08.021
You have yourself a deal.

53:08.021 --> 53:12.484
<i>♪ ♪</i>

53:12.484 --> 53:14.861
What's the quest?

53:14.861 --> 53:17.697
Sister Simone,

53:17.697 --> 53:24.371
you must locate...

53:24.371 --> 53:26.373
the Holy Grail.

53:27.582 --> 53:28.917
The what now?

53:28.917 --> 53:30.126
The Holy Grail.

53:30.126 --> 53:32.504
The cup of Christ.

53:32.504 --> 53:37.217
And after you find it,
I need you to destroy it.

53:37.217 --> 53:41.930
Once you do,
I will end my life.

53:41.930 --> 53:47.769
<i>♪ ♪</i>

53:47.769 --> 53:49.562
What do you say, Simone?

53:49.562 --> 53:53.358
Do you agree to the terms
and conditions of this quest?

53:53.358 --> 53:55.902
<i>♪ ♪</i>

53:55.902 --> 53:57.946
<i>[The Delfonics'
"Ready or Not"]</i>

53:57.946 --> 54:05.120
<i>♪ ♪</i>

54:05.870 --> 54:07.539
What should I call you?

54:07.539 --> 54:10.375
<i>* Ready or not,
here I come ♪</i>

54:10.375 --> 54:12.335
<i>♪ You can't hide ♪</i>

54:12.335 --> 54:15.255
<i>♪ Gonna love you ♪</i>

54:15.255 --> 54:18.466
<i>♪ And make you love me ♪</i>

54:18.466 --> 54:21.261
<i>♪ Ready or not, here I come ♪</i>

54:21.261 --> 54:23.054
<i>♪ You can't hide ♪</i>

54:23.054 --> 54:26.057
<i>♪ Gonna love you ♪</i>

54:26.057 --> 54:29.978
<i>♪ And make you love me ♪</i>

54:29.978 --> 54:32.731
<i>♪ You can't run away ♪</i>

54:32.731 --> 54:36.151
<i>♪ For this love I got,
oh baby ♪</i>

54:36.151 --> 54:41.406
<i>♪ Hey baby,
'cause I got a lot, yeah ♪</i>

54:41.406 --> 54:44.367
<i>♪ Anywhere you go ♪</i>

54:44.367 --> 54:47.579
<i>♪ My poor heart's gonna know,
oh, baby ♪</i>

54:47.579 --> 54:52.417
<i>♪ Hey, baby, you can't hide
from my love, oh, no ♪</i>

54:52.417 --> 54:55.253
<i>♪ Ready or not,
here I come ♪</i>

54:55.253 --> 54:57.088
<i>♪ You can't hide ♪</i>

54:57.088 --> 55:00.008
<i>♪ Gonna find you ♪</i>

55:00.008 --> 55:03.261
<i>♪ I'll keep you happy ♪</i>

55:03.261 --> 55:05.930
<i>♪ Ready or not,
here I come ♪</i>

55:05.930 --> 55:07.932
<i>♪ You can't hide ♪</i>

55:07.932 --> 55:10.935
<i>♪ Gonna love you ♪</i>

55:10.935 --> 55:13.438
<i>♪ I'll make you happy ♪</i>
